'''Cemal Yıldırım''' (1925–2009) was a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[philosopher]], author, educator, and researcher. He was a prolific author, having written 15 books (4 in English and 11 in Turkish) and numerous academic papers.
He has written extensively on the [[philosophy of science]] and the [[history of science]]. His popular books ''Bilimin Öncüleri'' ("Pioneers of Science") and ''Evrim Kuramı ve Bagnazlık'' ("[[Evolution|Theory of Evolution]] and Dogmatism") were widely read and discussed in [[Turkey]]. His book titled ''Matematiksel Düşünme'' ("Mathematical Thinking") was also very influential.
