{{BLP sources|date=January 2018}} {{Like resume|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox person |name = Julian Baggini |image = Julian Baggini-1.jpg |image_size = 200 |caption = Baggini in 2014 |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1968}} |birth_place = |nationality = British |education = PhD in philosophy (1996) |alma_mater = [[University College London]] |occupation = Philosopher, writer |website = {{URL|www.microphilosophy.net}} }}
'''Julian Baggini''' (born 1968) is a British philosopher, and the author of several books about philosophy written for a general audience. He is co-founder of ''[[The Philosophers' Magazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/bristol/hi/tv_and_radio/newsid_7920000/7920955.stm|title=Profile: Julian Baggini|publisher=[[BBC Online]]|accessdate=16 March 2012}}</ref>
Baggini was awarded a PhD in 1996 from [[University College London]] for a thesis on the philosophy of [[personal identity]].<ref name=davidhigham>{{cite web|title=Julian Baggini|url=http://www.davidhigham.co.uk/authors-dh/julian-baggini/|website=davidhigham|accessdate=30 October 2015}}</ref><ref name=UCL>{{cite web|title=1990 - 1999|url=https://www.ucl.ac.uk/philosophy/alumni/alumni-directory/1990-1999|website=UCL|accessdate=30 October 2015}}</ref>
